accounts.name: arcium_signer
docs: The Arcium signer who is making the deposit. Must be the owner of the Arcium user account.

accounts.name: arcium_user_account
docs: Arcium encrypted user account for the depositor. Must be initialized and active.

accounts.name: arcium_signer_wsol_ata
docs: Associated token account for the depositor's wrapped SOL holdings.

accounts.name: relayer
docs: The relayer who is facilitating this deposit. Receives relayer fees.

accounts.name: relayer_account
docs: Relayer account for the relayer. Must be initialized and active.

accounts.name: relayer_fees_pool
docs: Relayer fees pool where relayer fees are accumulated. Must be initialized.

accounts.name: public_commission_fees_pool
docs: Public commission fees pool where commission fees are accumulated. Must be initialized.

accounts.name: fees_configuration_account
docs: Fees configuration account containing relayer fees and commission fees settings.

accounts.name: program_information
docs: Program information account. Must be initialized and program must be active.

accounts.name: mixer_pool
docs: Mixer pool account for WSOL. Must be initialized and active.

accounts.name: mixer_pool_wsol_ata
docs: Associated token account for the mixer pool's wrapped SOL holdings.

accounts.name: zk_merkle_tree
docs: ZK merkle tree for tracking deposits. Must be initialized and have space available.

accounts.name: system_program
docs: System program for account creation and management.

accounts.name: token_program
docs: Token program interface for SPL token operations.

accounts.name: wsol_mint
docs: Wrapped SOL mint account. Must match the official WSOL mint address.

This event contains all the updated encrypted state after a successful deposit to
an existing token account structure.

types.name: NodeRef
docs: A reference to a node in the cluster.
The offset is to derive the Node Account.
The current_total_rewards is the total rewards the node has received so far in the current
epoch.

types.name: Output
docs: An output of a computation.
We currently don't support encrypted outputs yet since encrypted values are passed via
data objects.

types.name: Parameter
docs: A parameter of a computation.
We differentiate between plaintext and encrypted parameters and data objects.
Plaintext parameters are directly provided as their value.
Encrypted parameters are provided as an offchain reference to the data.
Data objects are provided as a reference to the data object account.
